        public URL getServiceURL(co.cask.cdap.proto.Id.Service service)
                  throws co.cask.cdap.common.NotFoundException,
                         IOException,
                         co.cask.cdap.common.UnauthenticatedException,
                         co.cask.cdap.security.spi.authorization.UnauthorizedException
        Deprecated. since 4.0.0. Please use getServiceURL(ServiceId) or getVersionedServiceURL(ServiceId) instead
        Gets a URL to call methods for a Service. If multiple versions exist, traffic to the URL will be distributed to each version according to routing strategy. If only one version exists, this version will always be reached with the URL.
        Parameters:
        service - ID of the service
        Returns:
        a URL to call methods of the service
        Throws:
        co.cask.cdap.common.NotFoundException - @throws NotFoundException if the app or service could not be found
        IOException - if a network error occurred
        co.cask.cdap.common.UnauthenticatedException - if the request is not authorized successfully in the gateway server
        co.cask.cdap.security.spi.authorization.UnauthorizedException
